WEBVTT

00:00.623 --> 00:02.924
My first kiss with Zoey was amazing,

00:02.925 --> 00:04.358
<i>and complicated.</i>

00:04.359 --> 00:05.794
Look, um...

00:05.795 --> 00:08.163
I know you're going through a lot right now.

00:08.164 --> 00:10.432
Getting divorced, being single,

00:10.433 --> 00:13.134
figuring out who you are on your own.

00:13.135 --> 00:15.070
Someone knows how to set a mood.

00:15.071 --> 00:17.272
I just mean...

00:17.273 --> 00:19.774
I'm okay taking this slow.

00:19.775 --> 00:21.843
I want to do this right.

00:21.844 --> 00:25.313
<i>My friends, as usual,
were completely supportive.</i>

00:25.314 --> 00:27.182
You're doing this all wrong!

00:27.183 --> 00:29.751
Ted, there are couples
in my kindergarten class

00:29.752 --> 00:31.820
who have moved faster than you two.

00:31.821 --> 00:33.755
Granted, their home lives are not great.

00:33.756 --> 00:34.989
Hey, I'm trying.

00:34.990 --> 00:36.858
I keep suggesting these big, romantic dates,

00:36.859 --> 00:38.777
and she keeps putting on the brakes.

00:38.778 --> 00:42.030
Like tonight, she wants me to
just come over and bake cookies.

00:42.031 --> 00:43.031
Oh.

00:43.032 --> 00:44.532
booty-call.

00:44.533 --> 00:46.201
Total booty-call.

00:46.202 --> 00:48.169
Private Booty, reporting for duty.

00:48.170 --> 00:49.704
That's crazy.

00:49.705 --> 00:50.872
She-She wants to bake.

00:50.873 --> 00:53.274
Guys booty-call girls after 2:00 a.m.

00:53.275 --> 00:56.511
with a drunkenly slurred, "What ya doing?"

00:56.512 --> 00:58.980
But when a lady booty-calls a guy,

00:58.981 --> 01:01.516
she invents a respectable excuse

01:01.517 --> 01:04.251
to mask the fact that she
wants to get stuck real good.

01:04.253 --> 01:05.787
It's called class, Ted.

01:05.788 --> 01:07.155
Wait. That...

01:07.156 --> 01:09.591
You think that's what she means by
"baking cookies"?

01:09.592 --> 01:10.809
Are you kidding?

01:10.810 --> 01:13.728
You're in the kitchen, it's getting hot,

01:13.729 --> 01:16.397
you start licking stuff
off each others' fingers.

01:16.398 --> 01:17.999
Before you know it, she's bent

01:18.000 --> 01:19.734
over the marble island,

01:19.735 --> 01:21.769
and you're spanking her
with a rubber spatula.

01:21.770 --> 01:23.605
And she's screaming, "Stop, Marshall, stop,"

01:23.606 --> 01:26.474
but that's just code for "harder!"

01:27.343 --> 01:28.543
Marshall's been in Minnesota

01:28.544 --> 01:29.644
a while, huh?

01:29.645 --> 01:30.945
So long!

01:30.946 --> 01:33.581
And now he's staying even longer.

01:33.582 --> 01:36.551
His mom has been having a really
hard time since the funeral.

01:36.552 --> 01:38.319
He's waiting on her hand and foot.

01:38.320 --> 01:39.354
But...

01:39.355 --> 01:40.355
it's Valentine's Day.

01:40.356 --> 01:41.823
It's not going to be the same

01:41.824 --> 01:43.758
<i>without the two of us watching
Predator together.</i>

01:43.759 --> 01:45.026
<i>I should explain.</i>

01:45.027 --> 01:46.928
<i>On their very first Valentine's Day,</i>

01:46.929 --> 01:50.231
<i>Marshall and Lily set out to watch
Sleepless in Seattle.</i>

01:50.232 --> 01:54.169
You know, I saw this in the theater,
like, five times,

01:54.170 --> 01:56.771
but I never got to see
it with the right girl.

01:56.772 --> 01:58.173
Aw...

01:58.174 --> 02:01.709
I'm so glad none of those
girls were right for you.

02:01.710 --> 02:03.278
What girls?

02:03.279 --> 02:05.780
If it bleeds, we can kill it.

02:05.781 --> 02:09.918
<i>Except Marshall's brothers had
taped over it with Predator.</i>

02:09.919 --> 02:11.085
Mmm.

02:11.086 --> 02:13.454
<i>And it became a tradition.</i>

02:13.455 --> 02:15.723
Wow, you sound really lonely.

02:15.724 --> 02:19.194
I am. Earlier today, I burst into tears...

02:19.195 --> 02:20.762
Shh. Daddy's talking now.

02:20.763 --> 02:23.531
Loneliness. The looming specter

02:23.532 --> 02:25.767
of Valentine's Day fast approaching.

02:25.768 --> 02:29.637
<i>The two key ingredients to my
favorite day of the year,</i>

02:29.638 --> 02:33.007
Desperation Day.

02:33.008 --> 02:35.109
That's not a thing. It's a thing.

02:35.110 --> 02:37.061
Much like Valentine's Day itself,

02:37.062 --> 02:39.380
Desperation Day dates
back thousands of years.

02:39.381 --> 02:41.199
<i> Weddings were forbidden</i>

02:41.200 --> 02:42.450
<i>under ancient Roman law,</i>

02:42.451 --> 02:44.886
<i>so Saint Valentine performed them in secret,</i>

02:44.887 --> 02:46.854
<i>under threat of death.</i>

02:46.855 --> 02:48.990
That's actually true. Wait, there's more.

02:48.991 --> 02:50.191
This won't be.

02:50.192 --> 02:52.026
<i>And right by Saint Valentine's side</i>

02:52.027 --> 02:55.630
<i>was his best bro, Saint Desperatius,</i>

02:55.631 --> 02:58.233
<i>there to pick off insecure bridesmaids.</i>

02:58.234 --> 02:59.634
Whoa. Check out that one.

02:59.635 --> 03:02.303
Her body is a perfect X.

03:02.304 --> 03:06.107
Player, play on. High V.

03:06.108 --> 03:08.376
Oh, Jupiter,

03:08.377 --> 03:10.929
what are your plans for me?

03:10.930 --> 03:13.548
15 and still unmarried.

03:14.783 --> 03:17.919
And I thought Pompeii was smokin'.

03:19.421 --> 03:22.073
Every woman wants a date on Valentine's Day.

03:22.074 --> 03:24.359
That neediness reaches its climax--

03:24.360 --> 03:26.828
what up-- on February 13.

03:26.829 --> 03:29.530
A magical night when a ten

03:29.531 --> 03:31.432
has the self-esteem of a four

03:31.433 --> 03:33.801
and the depraved enthusiasm of a two.

03:33.802 --> 03:36.771
Now, there's only one thing you can't do.

03:36.772 --> 03:38.439
Please say "widows."

03:38.440 --> 03:41.743
Wherever you are, or whoever you're under,

03:41.744 --> 03:46.281
<i>you must get home alone by 11:59 p.m.</i>

03:46.282 --> 03:49.417
Otherwise, you're on a
date on Valentine's Day.

03:49.418 --> 03:50.852
Barney, Desperation Day

03:50.853 --> 03:53.888
assumes that all single women
freak out about Valentine's Day.

03:53.889 --> 03:55.490
Which we do not.

03:55.491 --> 03:58.593
Case in point,
I will be spending February 13

03:58.594 --> 04:00.395
with some lovely single ladies from work...

04:00.396 --> 04:02.480
Trolls....who could care less

04:02.481 --> 04:04.399
about Valentine's Day. Lying trolls.

04:04.400 --> 04:06.600
And we will be celebrating
the fact that we don't have

04:06.601 --> 04:08.102
to spend it with some dippy guy

04:08.103 --> 04:10.238
carting around roses and
stuffed toys all night.

04:10.239 --> 04:11.339
Oh, no offense, Ted.

04:11.340 --> 04:14.709
And none was taken until just then.

04:15.280 --> 04:21.195
Transcript by Addic7ed.com

04:21.803 --> 04:27.655
www.addic7ed.com

04:27.690 --> 04:29.724
I decided to go to Minnesota

04:29.725 --> 04:31.059
to see Marshall.

04:31.060 --> 04:32.860
He shouldn't have to help his mom

04:32.861 --> 04:35.229
through this rough time all by himself.

04:35.230 --> 04:37.148
You losing your mind,
being alone in your apartment?

04:37.149 --> 04:38.299
I'm getting weird!

04:38.300 --> 04:40.468
<i> See, it started off</i>

04:40.469 --> 04:43.371
<i>with me throwing Marshall's
jersey on my body pillow.</i>

04:43.372 --> 04:47.375
<i>And, well, things kind of
spiraled from there.</i>

04:48.844 --> 04:51.746
I'm sorry I yelled like that before.

04:52.781 --> 04:55.183
I call him "Marshpillow." And he calls me...

04:55.184 --> 04:57.785
nothing because he's a pillow.

04:58.787 --> 05:00.955
Hey.

05:00.956 --> 05:03.157
Hey. How was "baking cookies" last night?

05:03.158 --> 05:04.826
<i> That was a tough question.</i>

05:04.827 --> 05:06.427
<i>You see...</i>

05:06.862 --> 05:08.129
Hi.

05:08.130 --> 05:10.565
Uh...

05:10.566 --> 05:13.067
Is that an overnight bag?

05:15.904 --> 05:17.872
You brought an overnight bag?

05:17.873 --> 05:19.807
You guys said I was definitely
going to spend the night.

05:19.808 --> 05:20.942
We said you were going to have sex.

05:20.943 --> 05:22.710
We didn't say, "Bring a carry-on."

05:22.711 --> 05:24.679
So how did Zoey react?

05:24.680 --> 05:27.315
She thought it was presumptuous
and asked me to leave.

05:27.316 --> 05:29.717
It's-It's not like I brought a ton of stuff.

05:29.718 --> 05:31.419
Were there slippers for the morning?

05:32.721 --> 05:35.056
Not slippers, exactly.

05:36.325 --> 05:38.793
They're called British morning socks.

05:39.661 --> 05:41.596
<i> This is such a nice surprise.</i>

05:41.597 --> 05:44.382
Marshall will be so happy.

05:44.383 --> 05:45.700
Oh...

05:45.701 --> 05:48.336
How are you holding up, Judy?

05:48.337 --> 05:49.404
Oh, I'm doin' okay.

05:49.405 --> 05:50.888
It gets a little lonely.

05:50.889 --> 05:53.808
My friends suggested a body pillow, but...

05:53.809 --> 05:55.810
I'm not a lunatic.

05:55.811 --> 05:57.061
Hey, Mom?

05:57.062 --> 05:58.713
I hate to be that guy,

05:58.714 --> 06:00.648
but I'm pretty sure it
was Hot Pocket o'clock,

06:00.649 --> 06:02.400
like, ten minutes ago.

06:02.401 --> 06:04.952
Lily. Lily.

06:04.953 --> 06:06.070
What are you doing here?

06:06.071 --> 06:07.822
I wanted to surprise you.

06:07.823 --> 06:09.574
Oh, my gosh. That's so sweet.

06:09.575 --> 06:11.409
I'm so glad you're here.

06:11.410 --> 06:13.194
Hey, um, before I forget, Mom,

06:13.195 --> 06:14.862
did you remember to get
more double-A batteries?

06:14.863 --> 06:15.963
Oh, they're upstairs, sweetie.

06:15.964 --> 06:17.665
Right next to your washed
and folded clothes.

06:17.666 --> 06:20.067
Oh, great, okay. I don't
want my Game Boy to crap out.

06:20.068 --> 06:22.120
I'm having the sickest
Dr. Mario run of my life.

06:22.121 --> 06:23.571
Okay. I'll be right back.

06:23.572 --> 06:24.639
I love you, Lily.

06:24.640 --> 06:25.640
Okay.

06:25.641 --> 06:26.791
You're the best, Mom.

06:26.792 --> 06:30.128
Aw... Anything for my baby bear.

06:30.129 --> 06:32.947
Get him out of my house.

06:37.632 --> 06:39.633
Take Marshall back to New York with you.

06:39.634 --> 06:40.700
Please, I am begging you.

06:40.701 --> 06:42.469
I thought he was here helping you.

06:42.470 --> 06:43.637
Well, he was, at first.

06:43.638 --> 06:44.871
But once he saw me starting

06:44.872 --> 06:46.706
to do better, he kind of regressed.

06:46.707 --> 06:49.509
He's been holed up in his
room for days at a time,

06:49.510 --> 06:50.844
playing old video games.

06:50.845 --> 06:54.181
I mean, he is having a pretty
sick Dr. Mario run, but...

06:55.216 --> 06:56.850
Uh, I'll talk to him.

06:56.851 --> 06:58.318
I want to be there for him,

06:58.319 --> 07:00.887
but it's like he's a teenager again.

07:00.888 --> 07:03.490
I even walked in on him abusing himself.

07:03.491 --> 07:04.691
Oh, God.

07:04.692 --> 07:05.859
There he was, on the bed,

07:05.860 --> 07:07.327
looking at old photos of his dad.

07:07.328 --> 07:10.697
That's emotional self-abuse,
don't you think?

07:13.901 --> 07:15.735
Hi. Hi.

07:15.736 --> 07:16.936
Listen,

07:16.937 --> 07:19.322
that was a dumb move for
me to just assume...

07:19.323 --> 07:20.540
No, no, I overreacted.

07:20.541 --> 07:24.244
I mean, I invited you over to
"bake cookies."

07:24.245 --> 07:25.879
We both knew what that meant.

07:25.880 --> 07:26.846
We totally did.

07:26.847 --> 07:28.248
I just, you know...

07:28.249 --> 07:30.317
I saw those slippers in your bag,

07:30.318 --> 07:31.351
and suddenly everything

07:31.352 --> 07:33.053
felt really serious.

07:33.054 --> 07:36.056
And... ever since, I've been asking myself,

07:36.057 --> 07:38.925
"Am I ready for this?"

07:38.926 --> 07:40.460
And...

07:40.461 --> 07:43.897
the answer is "yes."

07:48.152 --> 07:49.936
They're actually called
British morning socks.

07:49.937 --> 07:50.937
Yeah. Don't get in your own way.

07:50.938 --> 07:52.272
Right. Okay.

07:53.190 --> 07:55.325
Um, Marshall, your mom asked me

07:55.326 --> 07:56.543
to carry this up.

07:56.544 --> 07:58.712
She turned her ankle on your Hot Wheels.

07:58.713 --> 08:00.213
Is my track okay?

08:00.214 --> 08:02.782
It's fine, but, Marshall,

08:02.783 --> 08:05.452
I thought you were here
taking care of your mom.

08:05.453 --> 08:07.854
It seems like she's taking care of you.

08:07.855 --> 08:10.857
My mom loves to feel needed.

08:10.858 --> 08:12.192
Letting her take care of me

08:12.193 --> 08:14.561
is how I'm taking care of her.

08:15.363 --> 08:16.930
She's in a dark place, Lily.

08:16.931 --> 08:18.598
She needs this.

08:18.933 --> 08:20.000
Mom?

08:20.001 --> 08:21.301
You forgot my chocolate milk

08:21.302 --> 08:22.836
with the swirly straw!

08:22.837 --> 08:25.939
Oops. Comin' right up!

08:25.940 --> 08:28.275
Ow. Ow.

08:28.276 --> 08:29.609
She needs this.

08:29.610 --> 08:32.345
Marshall, tomorrow's Valentine's.

08:32.346 --> 08:35.081
Don't you want to be at home on our couch,

08:35.082 --> 08:37.150
cuddling up under a warm blanket,

08:37.150 --> 08:39.486
watching the Predator use his heat vision

08:39.486 --> 08:42.205
to stalk helpless prey?

