08:57.505 --> 08:59.906
<i>Well, baby, we could watch Predator here.</i>

08:59.907 --> 09:01.675
No, my mom can go rent it for us

09:01.676 --> 09:03.510
after she's done digging out the car.

09:03.511 --> 09:04.778
Marshall, your mom wants you out of here.

09:04.779 --> 09:05.812
What?

09:05.813 --> 09:07.714
Anything else, sweetie?

09:07.715 --> 09:10.483
Mom, d-do you want me to leave?

09:10.484 --> 09:12.719
Heavens to Bess, no!

09:12.720 --> 09:14.287
Of course not!

09:14.288 --> 09:15.355
But, Judy, you said...

09:15.356 --> 09:17.791
Oh, if Marshall could stay here forever,

09:17.792 --> 09:21.027
I would be the happiest mom in Minnesota.

09:25.116 --> 09:28.084
So Valentine's Day is tomorrow.

09:28.085 --> 09:30.453
Yeah. You know, there's
this new Italian restaurant

09:30.454 --> 09:32.672
on 79th that's supposed to be amazing.

09:32.673 --> 09:35.508
I would be happier having just
a simple, home-cooked meal.

09:35.509 --> 09:37.777
As long as it's with you.

09:37.778 --> 09:40.180
Tomorrow night, my place.

09:43.584 --> 09:45.819
I'm ready for this, Ted.

09:45.820 --> 09:46.786
I am in it

09:46.787 --> 09:48.304
for the long haul.

09:48.305 --> 09:51.691
I can't wait for our first
Valentine's Day as a couple.

09:53.160 --> 09:55.862
The one we'll remember for years.

09:57.932 --> 10:00.066
Isn't that great? Yeah, if you say so, yeah.

10:00.067 --> 10:01.167
What do you mean?

10:02.203 --> 10:03.937
Look, she just got out of a marriage, Ted.

10:03.938 --> 10:05.205
That's heavy.

10:05.206 --> 10:08.208
I'm kind of freaking out,
just listening to you.

10:08.209 --> 10:09.376
My heart is pounding,

10:09.377 --> 10:10.794
I'm hearing this weird clicking noise.

10:14.548 --> 10:16.516
Well, it's romantic, right?

10:16.517 --> 10:19.786
Zoey and I are getting
serious on Valentine's Day.

10:19.787 --> 10:22.389
See, that just amps up
the pressure even more.

10:22.390 --> 10:24.891
Boy, it's a good thing that you're sure.

10:24.892 --> 10:26.159
Who said I wasn't sure?

10:26.160 --> 10:28.795
I'm glad we're in a serious relationship.

10:28.796 --> 10:30.296
Right away.

10:30.297 --> 10:31.331
And if I screw this up,

10:31.332 --> 10:32.599
I'm the devil,

10:32.600 --> 10:34.100
because she's going through a divorce.

10:34.101 --> 10:35.985
But I'm not going to screw this up.

10:35.986 --> 10:38.438
So stop freaking out, Robin.

10:38.439 --> 10:39.973
Stop freaking out!

10:39.974 --> 10:42.876
<i>Kids, I'm not super proud
of what I did next.</i>

10:42.877 --> 10:44.160
Hi!

10:44.161 --> 10:45.712
I'm here to help Marshall.

10:47.982 --> 10:49.883
<i>Meanwhile, as Desperation Day</i>

10:49.884 --> 10:51.651
<i>turned into Desperation Night...</i>

10:51.652 --> 10:55.422
God, these girls are so
hungry for male attention.

10:55.423 --> 10:59.859
It is like being a hunter
and having the deer walk up,

10:59.860 --> 11:01.928
tie itself to the hood of your car

11:01.929 --> 11:03.496
and beg to get mounted.

11:03.497 --> 11:04.864
Barney, this is

11:04.865 --> 11:08.001
Bev and Anna, uh,
my coworkers and my friends.

11:08.002 --> 11:11.137
Bev, Anna, this is Barney,
a high-functioning sociopath

11:11.138 --> 11:13.039
and my ex.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.274
<i>Enchanté.</i>

11:14.275 --> 11:16.142
That's French for "What's with the purple?"

11:16.143 --> 11:17.477
Well, tomorrow is Valentine's Day,

11:17.478 --> 11:19.546
and everything is pink and red, so Bev

11:19.547 --> 11:20.880
very thoughtfully suggested

11:20.881 --> 11:23.883
that we wear purple to
show how little we care.

11:23.884 --> 11:25.952
I use, uh, colors to express emotion.

11:25.953 --> 11:27.454
Purple is for pride.

11:27.455 --> 11:29.589
It was a stupid idea.

11:29.590 --> 11:31.524
Bev, you look at me.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.827
<i>It's not a stupid idea.</i>

11:33.828 --> 11:35.728
Tonight, we are queens.

11:35.729 --> 11:38.364
And we don't care about some stupid,

11:38.365 --> 11:40.233
sexist, corporate holiday.

11:40.234 --> 11:41.885
Please!

11:41.886 --> 11:45.805
You might as well be dog-earing
a tear-stained bridal magazine

11:45.806 --> 11:47.774
while wolfing down the box of chocolates

11:47.775 --> 11:49.542
you had delivered to yourself at work

11:49.543 --> 11:51.644
from your "fiancé" who no one's ever met.

11:51.645 --> 11:53.680
Gerard is real!

11:54.548 --> 11:55.748
Oh!

11:56.817 --> 12:00.186
Ted... I thought you were going

12:00.187 --> 12:02.956
to talk to Marshall about
coming back to New York.

12:02.957 --> 12:06.459
Yeah, but, you know,
things move so fast in New York.

12:06.460 --> 12:10.263
Why not hang out here until at
least after Valentine's Day?

12:10.264 --> 12:12.265
Plus, we're helping Marshall's mom.

12:12.266 --> 12:14.417
Uh, Mrs. Eriksen,
we're running low on SunnyD!

12:14.418 --> 12:16.503
Is orange juice okay?

12:16.504 --> 12:18.805
No!

12:19.773 --> 12:23.409
Okay, when your "fiancé" Gerard comes back

12:23.410 --> 12:25.345
from fixing cleft palates in Peru,

12:25.346 --> 12:28.014
maybe snatch a photo of
the two of you together,

12:28.015 --> 12:29.549
and then I'll totally believe you.

12:29.550 --> 12:33.686
Well, he's going to Kenya after Peru, so...

12:33.687 --> 12:35.488
Hey, guys, so sorry I'm late.

12:35.489 --> 12:37.423
Hey. Hey, Nora. Uh, Nora, this is Barney.

12:37.424 --> 12:40.226
You want to see Anna beat
him in an arm wrestle?

12:40.227 --> 12:41.861
My elbow slipped!

12:43.464 --> 12:45.965
Marshall, I'm going home.

12:49.036 --> 12:50.937
What?

12:50.938 --> 12:53.907
I'm flying out tonight before the big storm,

12:53.908 --> 12:56.175
and I want you to come with me.

12:57.995 --> 13:00.680
I can't right now, 'cause my mom needs me.

13:00.681 --> 13:03.349
While I'm sure it's been really helpful

13:03.350 --> 13:04.751
for her to have you here

13:04.752 --> 13:07.954
<i>playing Super Mario Kart for
14 hours a day...</i>

13:07.955 --> 13:09.255
<i>You have Super Mario Kart?!</i>

13:09.256 --> 13:11.524
Hell, yeah.

13:11.525 --> 13:13.660
But your mom doesn't need you.

13:13.661 --> 13:15.562
Your life in New York needs you.

13:15.563 --> 13:18.765
It needs you really bad.

13:19.633 --> 13:21.601
Baby, don't go.

13:27.274 --> 13:30.159
Please come home soon.

13:33.881 --> 13:36.082
So, you were an Olympic gymnast?

13:36.083 --> 13:37.083
Silver medal.

13:37.084 --> 13:38.284
Ooh, sorry.

13:38.285 --> 13:40.486
Gold's the only thing that really counts.

13:40.487 --> 13:41.921
That's what my dad said.

13:41.922 --> 13:43.523
And she sticks the landing.

13:43.524 --> 13:46.292
Why don't you start stretching, and I'll...

13:46.293 --> 13:48.461
be right back.

13:48.462 --> 13:49.762
Hey, hey, sorry. Oh, hi.

13:49.763 --> 13:51.130
Quick question. Yeah.

13:51.131 --> 13:52.465
Why aren't you wearing
purple like your friends?

13:52.466 --> 13:54.968
Oh, I told them I forgot, but the truth is,

13:54.969 --> 13:56.703
I'm kind of protesting their protest.

13:57.371 --> 13:58.404
Can you keep a secret?

13:58.405 --> 13:59.238
Sure.

13:59.239 --> 14:01.140
I love Valentine's Day.

14:01.141 --> 14:03.309
Oh, my gosh! Me, too!

14:03.310 --> 14:05.979
Um, is it getting crowded in here,
'cause I think

14:05.980 --> 14:07.413
there are two peas in this pod?

14:07.414 --> 14:09.215
Oh, you're a gooey romantic, too?

14:09.216 --> 14:11.684
Guilty. This is embarrassing,

14:11.685 --> 14:15.088
but every year, I buy flowers
and a box of chocolates,

14:15.089 --> 14:17.290
even if I'm not with someone.

14:17.291 --> 14:19.692
Just in case, you know?

14:19.693 --> 14:21.894
We are pitiful. The worst.

14:23.130 --> 14:24.897
Although there is one
difference between you and me.

14:24.898 --> 14:27.100
What's that? I'm not saying any of this

14:27.101 --> 14:29.218
to get in your pants.

14:34.642 --> 14:37.410
I miss my dad, Ted.

14:38.178 --> 14:40.647
I miss him so much.

14:40.648 --> 14:42.148
I know.

14:43.851 --> 14:45.384
Um, when I was a kid,

14:45.385 --> 14:47.737
we would spend the summers
in the Upper Peninsula.

14:47.738 --> 14:50.356
And every year, we wouldn't get to the cabin

14:50.357 --> 14:52.558
till, like, the middle of the night.

14:52.559 --> 14:54.227
And so, it would be pitch black,

14:54.228 --> 14:56.195
<i>in the middle of the woods.</i>

14:56.196 --> 14:58.798
<i>And I could never see anything in
front of the headlights,</i>

14:58.799 --> 15:03.169
<i>but I always felt so safe 'cause
my dad was driving.</i>

15:03.170 --> 15:05.638
<i>He was like some sort of superhero</i>

15:05.639 --> 15:08.107
<i>who could just see way out
into the darkness.</i>

15:09.643 --> 15:11.844
Now he's just gone.

15:12.479 --> 15:15.048
And it's pitch black.

15:15.049 --> 15:18.317
And I can't see where I'm going.

15:18.318 --> 15:20.520
I can't see anything.

15:23.157 --> 15:24.524
All right, okay.

15:24.525 --> 15:25.925
I was playing you before.

15:25.926 --> 15:28.394
But I was really doing you a public service.

15:28.395 --> 15:30.296
It's February 13--

15:30.297 --> 15:33.666
a day many are now calling Desperation Day.

15:33.667 --> 15:35.068
It's kind of a thing.

15:35.069 --> 15:38.371
And you walking around,
saying you're a gooey romantic?

15:38.372 --> 15:41.240
It comes across a bit desperate.

15:41.241 --> 15:44.777
What's desperate about
knowing what you want?

15:44.778 --> 15:46.679
Look, life is really short, Barney.

15:46.680 --> 15:48.715
Who wants to spend Valentine's Day alone,

15:48.716 --> 15:50.383
distracting yourself from the fact

15:50.384 --> 15:53.886
that nobody loves you with
some sad little activity?

15:53.887 --> 15:56.622
Um, or you could be in the 47th Semi-Annual

15:56.623 --> 15:59.659
Laser Tag Tournament in Poughkeepsie.

15:59.660 --> 16:02.628
I have no idea what any of those words mean.

16:02.629 --> 16:05.198
Hey, I'm all stretched out!

16:06.867 --> 16:09.802
Here's the first thing you
need to know about laser tag.

16:09.803 --> 16:11.938
Thanks a lot for coming out here, man.

16:11.939 --> 16:13.406
Yeah.

16:13.407 --> 16:16.609
Hey, are-are you sure it's okay with Zoey

16:16.610 --> 16:18.644
that you're here for Valentine's Day?

16:18.645 --> 16:21.914
Well, I mean, technically,
she doesn't know yet.

16:21.915 --> 16:22.749
What?

16:22.750 --> 16:24.083
Things with Zoey

16:24.084 --> 16:25.785
are moving really fast,

16:25.786 --> 16:28.454
and the divorce just makes
everything more complicated.

16:28.455 --> 16:30.990
I just, I needed to take a step back.

16:30.991 --> 16:32.558
You're not taking a step back.

16:32.559 --> 16:34.060
You're running away.

16:34.061 --> 16:35.328
And hiding out here,

16:35.329 --> 16:37.930
hiding out here is not gonna solve anything.

16:37.931 --> 16:38.898
You're just

16:38.899 --> 16:40.366
holed up in Minnesota

16:40.367 --> 16:43.536
because you're too scared
to face reality, and it's...

16:46.106 --> 16:49.909
We got to go back to New York, tonight.

16:49.910 --> 16:52.111
We're snowed in. Lily got the last flight.

16:52.112 --> 16:54.147
So, we drive. It's time.

16:54.148 --> 16:56.449
It's time to get back to real life.

16:56.450 --> 16:59.152
It's time to grow up.

16:59.153 --> 17:00.319
Yeah.

17:00.320 --> 17:01.587
Mom!

17:01.588 --> 17:04.457
Can you make us some PB
and J's for the road?

17:04.458 --> 17:05.758
Crusts cut off.

17:05.759 --> 17:07.827
Crusts cut off!

17:07.828 --> 17:09.529
No, Ted. What are we...?

17:10.964 --> 17:13.532
We're men.

17:14.635 --> 17:16.769
Mom!

17:16.770 --> 17:19.939
Leave the crusts on!

17:24.280 --> 17:26.582
They forced their opponents to scatter,
picking them off,

17:26.583 --> 17:29.402
one by one, in a swift
and merciless slaughter.

17:31.738 --> 17:33.472
became the 2010 Tri-County Champions.

17:34.473 --> 17:37.342
Wow. Laser tag sounds brilliant!

17:37.343 --> 17:38.593
Oh, it is.

17:38.594 --> 17:40.495
Plus, if you win, you get free pizza!

17:40.496 --> 17:43.198
This is my teammate for tomorrow.

17:43.199 --> 17:44.966
Oh, yeah, I agreed to that.

17:44.967 --> 17:46.901
Where are Bev and Anna?

17:46.902 --> 17:47.769
Well...

17:47.770 --> 17:49.337
So, we're taking off.

17:49.338 --> 17:50.372
What?

17:50.373 --> 17:51.573
Those guys are gonna

17:51.574 --> 17:53.408
buy us hot dogs at Grey's Papaya.

17:53.409 --> 17:55.243
What...? So that's it?

17:55.244 --> 17:59.247
A couple of white Urkels offer
you sausages, and you're gone?

17:59.248 --> 18:01.182
What about the sisterhood?

18:01.183 --> 18:03.151
Solidarity? The color purple?

18:03.152 --> 18:05.687
But tomorrow's Valentine's Day.

18:05.688 --> 18:07.322
I thought we didn't care
about Valentine's Day.

18:07.323 --> 18:09.624
Look, Robin, you'll find someone, too.

18:09.625 --> 18:11.059
You're a queen.

18:11.060 --> 18:12.594
You've got so much to offer.

18:12.595 --> 18:14.496
Maybe do something with that hair.

18:16.098 --> 18:17.265
I'm telling you.

18:17.266 --> 18:18.600
The power of Valentine's Day.

18:18.601 --> 18:22.404
I'm Huey Lewis, and you just heard the news.

18:23.272 --> 18:24.773
Well, I think I'm heading out, too.

18:24.774 --> 18:27.192
What? No, don't go!
You want to see a magic trick?!

18:27.193 --> 18:29.510
It's late, and I have a date with my pillow.

18:29.511 --> 18:31.679
I mean, not literally. I'm not a lunatic.

18:32.415 --> 18:33.615
Boy Scout Troop 15

18:33.616 --> 18:34.849
doesn't stand a chance.

18:34.850 --> 18:36.751
Bye.

18:36.752 --> 18:38.453
Mm.

18:42.358 --> 18:45.627
Speaking of the power of Valentine's Day...

18:45.628 --> 18:47.295
What are you talking about?

18:47.296 --> 18:48.563
Oh, come on.

18:48.564 --> 18:49.964
It's-It's past midnight.

18:49.965 --> 18:52.467
Desperation Day has come and gone,

18:52.468 --> 18:55.670
and you have neither gone nor come.

18:56.372 --> 18:58.173
You know why?

18:58.174 --> 18:59.307
You like Nora.

18:59.308 --> 19:00.542
No, I don't. She's gross.

19:00.543 --> 19:02.610
<i>Oh... You like her.</i>

19:02.611 --> 19:05.113
You think she smells like rain.

19:05.114 --> 19:06.948
Whatever you say.

19:06.949 --> 19:08.266
Oh, hey, Nora.

19:08.267 --> 19:09.734
Nora...

19:18.727 --> 19:20.728
Here's a secret.

19:20.729 --> 19:24.632
I couldn't see worth a damn, either, buddy.

19:24.633 --> 19:28.770
I just kept driving forward,
hoping for the best.

19:30.539 --> 19:32.624
Look out!

19:32.625 --> 19:33.942
Gotcha.

19:42.318 --> 19:44.285
<i>And so we drove through the night,</i>

19:44.286 --> 19:46.554
<i>out of Desperation Day and into Valentine's.</i>

19:46.555 --> 19:49.290
<i>And there was no trace of my
little freak out, except...</i>

19:49.291 --> 19:52.193
Really? An overnight bag
for your own living room?

19:54.430 --> 19:56.831
Looks like we got a matching set.

19:56.832 --> 19:59.767
Well, that was kind of presumptuous.

20:02.671 --> 20:04.822
♪ The ground was shaking like ♪

20:04.823 --> 20:07.141
Robin, where are you?

20:07.142 --> 20:09.043
Those Boy Scouts have grown
a foot since last year.

20:09.044 --> 20:10.211
They're terrifying!

20:10.212 --> 20:11.613
Oh, yeah.

20:11.614 --> 20:13.181
Change of plans.

20:13.182 --> 20:14.716
Happy Valentine's Day.

20:14.717 --> 20:16.784
Hap...? Hey, Barney.

20:16.785 --> 20:18.953
Robin told me to meet you guys here.

20:18.954 --> 20:21.322
<i>And that's how, for the first
time in his life,</i>

20:21.323 --> 20:24.459
<i>Barney Stinson wound up on a
date on Valentine's Day.</i>

20:25.728 --> 20:26.811
Oh!

20:29.798 --> 20:31.032
You will be avenged.

20:33.869 --> 20:35.470
♪ It's good to see you ♪

20:35.471 --> 20:37.205
Come on! Come on!

20:37.206 --> 20:38.673
Kill me! I'm here! Kill me!

20:38.674 --> 20:40.975
♪ It's good to see you though ♪

20:40.976 --> 20:43.511
Baby, you're back.

20:43.512 --> 20:45.280
Happy Valentine's Day, Lily Pad. Oh.

